  "texts": [
    "As such, a precise and timely diagnosis is of paramount importance.",
    "A critical factor in diagnosis is radiological data, as chest X-rays routinely acquired as as standard care and can aid in differentiating various types of pneumonia.",
    "However, rapid interpretation of radiographic images often proves infeasible, especially in resource-constrained settings where the incidence and mortality of pediatric pneumonia are highest.",
    "To address this, we also investigated the effectiveness of our transfer learning framework in classifying pediatric chest X-rays to detect pneumonia and further discern between viral and bacterial pneumonia, with the aim of facilitating rapid referrals for children in need of urgent interventions.",
    "Medical imaging differencesPneumonia is a lung infection instigated by bacteria, viruses, or fungi."
  ]
